'I am thrilled because I am moving on with my life. I am taking away the old and bringing in the new and I just can't wait to see what it brings.'

Part of that future will include running the Boston Marathon, she said.

'It's one of my biggest goals,' she said. 'I will run the Boston Marathon, definitely.'

Before she lost the limb on Monday, DiMartino tickled her supporters by posting a break-up letter to the leg on Facebook, hosting a 'left leg last supper' and writing, 'It's not you, it's me' across her shin. 

